               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors in Text I; names of the commissioner and the scribe in Text II; a few lines in the incipit pages of Text I and II, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text Text I and II; some abbreviations, elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numbers; some other words, e.g., ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 10va, 11rb, 15ra), tägśaṣ (fol. 22rb), sälam (fols. 80va, 125ra), wä-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g., fols. 83vb, 84rb, 86rb), mǝlṭan (e.g., fols. 125ra, 126ra, 127ra).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="149rb"/>Fol. 149rb: ስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ ጽሒፈ፡ መጽሐፎሙ፡ ለ፲ወ፪አርድእት፡ አነ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወጊጉይ፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡፡<foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 149rb: May praise be to God who made me finish the writing of the Book of the 12 Disciples. I am sinner and wicked Wäldä Śǝllase. </foreign>
                        <note>The colophon mentions Wäldä Śǝllase as the scribe only for Text I.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
